      "\n",
      "----- EXPERIMENT 1: THE ATOMIC PROMPT -----\n",
      "Let's start with the most basic unit: a single instruction.\n",
      "\n",
      "Atomic Prompt: 'Write a short poem about programming.'\n",
      "Token Count: 8\n",
      "\n",
      "Generating response...\n",
      "\n",
      "Response:\n",
      "Lines of logic, clearly spun,\n",
      "A problem faced, a task begun.\n",
      "With syntax strict and patient hand,\n",
      "You build a world, at your command.\n",
      "\n",
      "A bug appears, a cryptic flaw,\n",
      "You chase it down, defying law.\n",
      "Then suddenly, the errors flee,\n",
      "And perfect code runs wild and free.\n",
      "\n",
      "----- EXPERIMENT 2: ADDING CONSTRAINTS -----\n",
      "Now let's add constraints to our atomic prompt and observe the difference.\n",
      "\n",
      "Prompt 1: 'Write a short poem about programming.'\n",
      "Token Count: 8\n",
      "Latency: 4.6291 seconds\n",
      "Response:\n",
      "A blank screen waits, a thought takes flight,\n",
      "To bring an idea into light.\n",
      "With careful logic, line by line,\n",
      "A new design, I intertwine.\n",
      "\n",
      "A blinking cursor, stark and bright,\n",
      "Errors surface, dark as night.\n",
      "A missing brace, a syntax pain,\n",
      "Debug, refactor, try again.\n",
      "\n",
      "Then sudden insight, clear and true,\n",
      "The silent gears begin anew.\n",
      "A concept born, a task complete,\n",
      "The humming code, a victory sweet.\n",
      "\n",
      "Prompt 2: 'Write a short poem about programming in 4 lines.'\n",
      "Token Count: 12\n",
      "Latency: 1.9659 seconds\n",
      "Response:\n",
      "Lines of logic, byte by byte,\n",
      "We shape a world, both dark and bright.\n",
      "With syntax strict and errors grand,\n",
      "A silent power in our hand.\n",
      "\n",
      "Prompt 3: 'Write a short haiku about programming using only simple words.'\n",
      "Token Count: 13\n",
      "Latency: 5.7269 seconds\n",
      "Response:\n",
      "Type words on screen,\n",
      "Watch the small program run now,\n",
      "Lights blink, it works well.\n",
      "\n",
      "----- EXPERIMENT 3: MEASURING THE ROI CURVE -----\n",
      "Let's explore the relationship between prompt complexity and output quality.\n"
